James de Villiers, News24 Roads have been closed around Nyanga Junction where an apparent attempted cash in transit heist turned into a hostage drama. (Supplied) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Three people have been released from a hostage drama inside the Shoprite supermarket in Nyanga Junction on Monday afternoon, a police spokesperson said.Police are unable to estimate how many people are inside the building or how many armed robbers are involved, Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana told News24.A hostage&nbsp;negotiator was deployed to the scene on Monday morning, but Rwexana said there was no communication between police and the robbers."We do not know what their demands are," Rwexana said. She said no additional shots have been fired since the shooting earlier the morning.City of Cape Town mayoral committee member for safety, JP Smith, said he received reports that four people, including a private security guard, have been injured but could not confirm.&nbsp; He said police asked metro police to vacate the premises. &nbsp;Minister of police Fikile Mbalula tweeted that the a special task force has been sent to the scene.&ldquo;The situation is under SAPS control,&rdquo;&nbsp; he said.A Special Task Force with a hostage negotiator has been sent in to Nyanga junction. The situation there is still under SAPS control. pic.twitter.com/0ps5ZAJUST24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.